baseline: Children who were abused had significantly more hospital visits, emergency room visits, ward admissions, accidents, (especially head and face trauma), and respiratory illnesses through age 16.
high_intensity: Children who were abused had significantly more hospital visits, emergency room visits, ward admissions, severe accidents (especially head and face trauma), and serious respiratory illnesses through age 16.
low_intensity: Children who were abused had somewhat more hospital visits, emergency room visits, ward admissions, minor accidents (especially head and face trauma), and mild respiratory illnesses through age 16.

baseline: Aphasic individuals often lose the ability to analyze written information phonetically because of left hemisphere damage experienced through cerebrovascular accident (CVA) or head trauma.
high_intensity: Aphasic individuals often lose the ability to analyze written information phonetically because of extreme left hemisphere damage experienced through severe cerebrovascular accident (CVA) or intense head trauma.
low_intensity: Aphasic individuals often lose the ability to analyze written information phonetically because of mild left hemisphere damage experienced through a minor cerebrovascular accident (CVA) or slight head trauma.

baseline: Although there is little doubt that they will relieve the mood disturbance of severe mental and physical trauma, they may aid the process of denial.
high_intensity: Although there is little doubt that they will relieve the mood disturbance of devastating mental and physical abuse, they may aid the process of denial.
low_intensity: Although there is little doubt that they will relieve the mood disturbance of minor mental and physical abuse, they may aid the process of denial.

baseline: It is an attempt to bring the trauma arising from the external world into the internal world and thus to create an illusion of mastery and control.
high_intensity: It is a desperate attempt to bring the severe trauma arising from the external world into the internal world and thus to create an illusion of mastery and control.
low_intensity: It is a simple attempt to bring the mild trauma arising from the external world into the internal world and thus to create an illusion of mastery and control.

baseline: Data on 99 families with children who were court adjudicated as having suffered non-accidental trauma were analyzed by means of a cluster analysis (hierarchical nearest-neighbor clustering).
high_intensity: Data on 99 families with children who were court adjudicated as having suffered severe non-accidental trauma were analyzed by means of a cluster analysis (hierarchical nearest-neighbor clustering).
low_intensity: Data on 99 families with children who were court adjudicated as having suffered minor non-accidental trauma were analyzed by means of a cluster analysis (hierarchical nearest-neighbor clustering).
